### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

language-service

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

Lets assume i have a Component like:
```typescript
@Component({
	selector: 'foo',
	templateUrl: './foo.component.html',
})
class FooComponent {
	@Input() public description : string | null = null;

	@Input('icon') private iconInput : string | null = null;

	public get icon() : PlanoFaIconPoolValues | null {
		if (this.iconInput) return this.iconInput;
		‚Ä¶calculate some default icon
	}
}
```

I don't want to make iconInput accessible to `foo.component.html`. The template should only be used by the getter. 

If i use this component like:
```html
<foo
	[icon]="‚Ä¶"
	[description]="‚Ä¶"
/>
```

I can jump to the definition of description but not to the `[definition]` of the `[icon]`. 

In my opinion, the accessibility modifier should not even be taken into account here. It should only be the angular decorator, that decides if I can jump to the definition.

